race.comment: SUIT OF WANDS (5) is a maiden but he has more upside than most of his rivals here. The untapped 4YO has been back to the trials since chasing a smart one in town last starts. This is much easier, he's drawn well with Todd Pannell in the saddle and he can win. SANDPIPER (2) went close to making it three wins in a row last start. She is racing in career-best form and will be within striking distance. She can definitely win again. SPEC RAIDER (3) returns to her favourite track and distance and is another that will be hard to beat if the luck goes her way. BUSH INFERENCE (6) is capable on his day and is one to include in exotics, while CHARTIN (4) boasts a likable on-speed racing style that will give him a sneaky top three chance again.
